meta {
  name: RAG
  type: http
  seq: 2
}

post {
  url: {{ai_url}}/rag
  body: json
  auth: none
}

body:json {
  {
    "question": "How does the order process work?",
    "contextId": "marketspace-docs"
  }
}

docs {
  ## RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation)

  Answers a question by first searching the vector store for relevant documents,
  then using those documents as context for the LLM to generate a grounded answer.

  ### Body fields
  | Field     | Description |
  |-----------|-------------|
  | question  | Natural language question |
  | contextId | Vector store namespace to search (e.g. "marketspace-docs", "policies", "catalog") |

  ### Built-in context IDs
  | contextId         | What's stored there |
  |-------------------|----------------------|
  | marketspace-docs  | Order lifecycle, shipping, payment, cancellation docs (auto-seeded on startup) |
  | catalog           | Product catalog (seeded by CatalogSeeder on startup if Catalog API is reachable) |
  | any custom        | Documents you ingested via `POST /rag/ingest` |

  ### Response
  ```json
  {
    "answer": "Orders in MarketSpace go through: Created → Processing → ReadyForDelivery → ...",
    "sources": ["Orders in MarketSpace go from Created to Processing..."]
  }
  ```
}

